title: fanoutqa: What are the largest moons of Earth, Mars, Jupiter, and Saturn, and what are their diameters in kilometers? (f384f0d0b3af54e4)

chat_history.content: What are the largest moons of Earth, Mars, Jupiter, and Saturn, and what are their diameters in kilometers?

The largest moons of Earth, Mars, Jupiter, and Saturn are as follows:

- Earth: Luna (Moon), diameter: 3,474 km
- Mars: Phobos, diameter: 22.2 km. Phobos is followed by Deimos, which has a diameter of about 12.6 km.
- Jupiter: Ganymede, diameter: 5,262 km
- Saturn: Titan, diameter: 5,150 km

functions.name: delegate
functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

instructions.description: Detailed instructions on what your helper should do to help you.
